WEBVTT

00:00:12.583 --> 00:00:15.042
"November 1, 2024"       "Floor 1: Town of Beginnings"

00:00:26.083 --> 00:00:27.250
This is...

00:00:27.250 --> 00:00:28.458
...amazing.

00:00:28.458 --> 00:00:29.833
Yeah.

00:00:30.667 --> 00:00:32.375
It's like this every day.

00:00:33.542 --> 00:00:36.083
How is Yui feeling?

00:00:36.083 --> 00:00:40.833
She got a good night's sleep,
and you can see it's helped.

00:00:41.708 --> 00:00:43.667
Has this ever happened before?

00:00:43.667 --> 00:00:45.042
We don't know.

00:00:45.458 --> 00:00:49.375
When we found her, she was wandering
in the forest on floor 22.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:52.792
She seems to have
lost her memories.

00:00:52.792 --> 00:00:54.000
Oh my.

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.000
So we came to the
Town of Beginnings.

00:00:58.958 --> 00:01:02.292
We thought someone here
might know her.

00:01:02.292 --> 00:01:04.500
Does she look familiar at all?

00:01:05.667 --> 00:01:07.583
I'm sorry, but I don't think

00:01:07.583 --> 00:01:10.333
she's one of the kids from
the Town of Beginnings.

00:01:11.292 --> 00:01:12.792
When the game started,

00:01:12.792 --> 00:01:15.750
most of the children suffered
terrible psychological trauma.

00:01:16.167 --> 00:01:19.125
I couldn't just stand by
and do nothing,

00:01:19.125 --> 00:01:21.625
so I started living with
them in this church.

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:27.000
Every day, I walk around the town
to see if anyone needs my help.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:29.708
But I've never seen
anyone like her.

00:01:30.542 --> 00:01:31.875
I see...

00:01:35.958 --> 00:01:38.083
Hello. I am Yulier.

00:01:39.083 --> 00:01:41.167
You're with the Army, right?

00:01:41.542 --> 00:01:43.750
Are you here to protest what
happened yesterday?

00:01:43.750 --> 00:01:46.250
Not at all. It's the reverse.

00:01:46.667 --> 00:01:49.167
As a matter of fact,
I wanted to thank you.

00:01:50.833 --> 00:01:53.542
I've come to request something
of you two today.

00:01:54.292 --> 00:01:55.458
Request?

00:02:07.417 --> 00:02:11.833
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:02:12.167 --> 00:02:17.667
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:28.542
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:02:28.875 --> 00:02:33.875
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:02:34.208 --> 00:02:38.583
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:41.333
<i>Out of control</i>

00:02:41.667 --> 00:02:46.917
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:02:47.250 --> 00:02:52.083
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:02:52.417 --> 00:02:58.583
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:02:58.917 --> 00:03:02.542
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:03:02.875 --> 00:03:07.833
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:03:08.167 --> 00:03:13.833
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:03:14.750 --> 00:03:17.208
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:03:17.542 --> 00:03:22.917
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:03:26.042 --> 00:03:30.042
"Yui's Heart"

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:33.500
Originally, we...

00:03:33.833 --> 00:03:36.500
No, our guild leader, Thinker,

00:03:36.500 --> 00:03:40.833
never wanted it to be the dictatorial
organization that it's become.

00:03:41.417 --> 00:03:43.500
We just wanted to share
information and food

00:03:43.500 --> 00:03:47.250
evenly among as many
players as possible.

00:03:47.250 --> 00:03:49.583
But the Army grew too large.

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:53.542
Yes, there were multiple internal power
struggles, and a man named Kibaou

00:03:53.542 --> 00:03:55.542
ended up with a great
deal of power.

00:03:56.667 --> 00:03:59.292
Kibaou and his faction have
become dominant,

00:03:59.292 --> 00:04:02.083
monopolizing all of the best
monster spawn points

00:04:02.083 --> 00:04:06.875
and have gone so far as to extort people
under the pretext of collecting taxes.

00:04:07.708 --> 00:04:12.958
But people started criticizing Kibaou for
neglecting his obligation to clear the game.

00:04:12.958 --> 00:04:18.875
So he sent the highest-level players
under his command to the front lines.

00:04:20.125 --> 00:04:21.375
Corvatz...

00:04:24.208 --> 00:04:27.458
Because of that fiasco, Kibaou
was strongly denounced,

00:04:27.708 --> 00:04:31.917
and we were close to dismissing
him from the guild.

00:04:32.417 --> 00:04:37.083
Desperate, he resorted to drastic
measures, setting a trap for Thinker.

00:04:38.833 --> 00:04:42.458
Thinker's been stranded
deep inside a dungeon!

00:04:43.333 --> 00:04:44.667
Doesn't he have a teleport crystal?

00:04:45.958 --> 00:04:47.375
Don't tell me he's unarmed.

00:04:48.333 --> 00:04:50.333
He was too trusting.

00:04:50.750 --> 00:04:54.542
He believed Kibaou when he said
he only wanted to talk unarmed.

00:04:54.833 --> 00:04:56.333
That was three days ago.

00:04:56.333 --> 00:04:58.875
Three days? What's happened to him?

00:04:58.875 --> 00:05:02.083
He's in the depths of a significantly
high-level dungeon.

00:05:02.083 --> 00:05:04.000
He seems to be stuck there...

00:05:04.625 --> 00:05:07.500
As his second-in-command,
this is my responsibility.

00:05:08.500 --> 00:05:12.500
But my level isn't high
enough to reach him.

00:05:12.500 --> 00:05:14.708
And Kibaou is using his influence

00:05:14.708 --> 00:05:16.958
to prevent the rest of
the Army from helping.

00:05:17.500 --> 00:05:22.792
And then I heard that two incredibly
high-powered players had come here.

00:05:22.792 --> 00:05:24.875
And so I'm asking for your help.

00:05:25.792 --> 00:05:27.667
Kirito, Asuna...

00:05:27.667 --> 00:05:31.750
Would you please come and
save Thinker with me?

00:05:34.167 --> 00:05:38.750
If there's something we can do,
we'd like to help you out.

00:05:39.292 --> 00:05:42.625
But we do need to
verify your story...

00:05:42.625 --> 00:05:45.833
I know that I'm
asking a lot of you!

00:05:45.833 --> 00:05:49.292
But when I think about
him trapped in there,

00:05:49.875 --> 00:05:52.125
I feel like I'm losing my mind...

00:05:55.708 --> 00:05:57.250
It's okay, Mommy.

00:05:58.625 --> 00:06:00.792
She's telling the truth.

00:06:00.792 --> 00:06:03.708
Y-Yui, you can tell?

00:06:04.042 --> 00:06:05.333
Yeah.

00:06:05.333 --> 00:06:07.625
I can't explain why...

00:06:08.083 --> 00:06:09.083
But I know.

00:06:15.958 --> 00:06:19.542
I'd rather regret trusting someone
than regret doubting them.

00:06:20.375 --> 00:06:21.042
Let's go.

00:06:21.042 --> 00:06:22.583
It'll work out.

00:06:22.917 --> 00:06:23.917
Right?

00:06:26.292 --> 00:06:28.500
You're always so laid-back.

00:06:29.792 --> 00:06:32.292
We'll do what we can.

00:06:34.375 --> 00:06:36.083
Thank you.

00:06:36.083 --> 00:06:40.708
I know how it feels to want to
save someone you care for.

00:06:42.167 --> 00:06:43.958
Stay here for a little while, okay?

00:06:43.958 --> 00:06:45.417
No, I'm coming too.

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:48.833
Yui, stay here with me, okay?

00:06:48.833 --> 00:06:50.250
No!

00:06:50.250 --> 00:06:52.792
Ah, this must be her rebellious phase.

00:06:52.792 --> 00:06:54.375
Don't be silly.

00:06:54.625 --> 00:06:57.500
Yui, the place we're
headed is dangerous.

00:06:58.542 --> 00:07:00.250
I'm going too!

00:07:00.750 --> 00:07:04.250
"Floor 1: Town of Beginnings"       "Black Iron Castle"

00:07:04.583 --> 00:07:08.042
To think a dungeon like this was
under the Town of Beginnings.

00:07:08.042 --> 00:07:12.292
There wasn't anything like this during
the beta test. I totally missed it.

00:07:12.292 --> 00:07:16.458
It probably opens further,
as the floors above are cleared.

00:07:16.458 --> 00:07:20.125
Kibaou planned to
keep it to himself.

00:07:20.125 --> 00:07:22.958
Exclusive access to spawns
can be lucrative...

00:07:22.958 --> 00:07:27.083
But it's mostly powerful level-60
monsters that spawn here.

00:07:27.083 --> 00:07:29.292
So he wasn't able to
do much hunting.

00:07:32.208 --> 00:07:33.292
This is the entrance.

00:07:37.042 --> 00:07:38.542
I'm not scared!

00:07:39.250 --> 00:07:40.458
It's okay.

00:07:40.458 --> 00:07:43.000
She's much tougher
than she looks.

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:46.000
Yeah. I'm sure she'll be a fine
swordswoman someday!

00:07:49.792 --> 00:07:50.958
Let's go then.

00:08:12.792 --> 00:08:15.208
I'm sorry for not helping.

00:08:15.208 --> 00:08:17.750
No, this is his kind of thing.

00:08:17.750 --> 00:08:19.125
Just let him be.

00:08:21.708 --> 00:08:24.375
We're pretty far down.
Are we almost there?

00:08:25.875 --> 00:08:28.667
Thinker hasn't moved
from this position.

00:08:28.667 --> 00:08:31.292
I think he's in a safe zone.

00:08:32.125 --> 00:08:35.042
If we can reach it, we can
use a teleport crystal.

00:08:35.042 --> 00:08:38.042
Oh man, I really
fought up a storm!

00:08:38.042 --> 00:08:39.125
Sorry about that.

00:08:39.125 --> 00:08:41.292
No, I enjoyed it.

00:08:41.292 --> 00:08:42.958
And they dropped some items too.

00:08:43.917 --> 00:08:45.500
Did you get anything good?

00:08:49.375 --> 00:08:52.167
--Wh-What is this?
--Scavenged toad meat.

00:08:52.167 --> 00:08:53.667
Y-You mean those frogs?

00:08:53.667 --> 00:08:57.917
They say the stranger it is,
the better it tastes. Cook it up later.

00:08:57.917 --> 00:08:59.292
No way!

00:09:02.167 --> 00:09:03.917
Wh-What are you doing?

00:09:04.542 --> 00:09:05.792
Damn it!

00:09:05.792 --> 00:09:07.208
Fine then...

00:09:07.208 --> 00:09:08.875
How about these?

00:09:09.542 --> 00:09:13.333
--No! No, no, no, no!
--Asuna, it's good meat!

00:09:13.333 --> 00:09:16.833
--Get rid of it!
--But it's delicious!

00:09:16.833 --> 00:09:18.250
You smiled.

00:09:20.208 --> 00:09:22.292
It's the first time you've
smiled, big sister!

00:09:32.625 --> 00:09:34.250
Come on, let's go.

00:09:47.375 --> 00:09:48.708
There's the safe zone.

00:09:51.125 --> 00:09:52.583
There's one player inside.

00:09:54.042 --> 00:09:55.167
Thinker!

00:09:55.167 --> 00:09:56.583
W-Wait...

00:10:02.625 --> 00:10:04.292
Yulier!

00:10:05.458 --> 00:10:06.750
Thinker!

00:10:08.458 --> 00:10:09.458
Stay back!

00:10:09.833 --> 00:10:11.208
That corridor is...

00:10:14.583 --> 00:10:15.625
Stop!

00:10:15.625 --> 00:10:17.417
Yulier, come back!

00:10:31.375 --> 00:10:32.458
Yulier.

00:10:32.458 --> 00:10:35.500
Please take her and
retreat to the safe zone.

00:10:35.500 --> 00:10:37.250
R-Right.

00:10:37.250 --> 00:10:38.417
Mommy...

00:10:38.417 --> 00:10:39.417
Let's go.

00:10:59.667 --> 00:11:00.667
Asuna,

00:11:00.667 --> 00:11:04.208
use a teleport crystal to get Yui
and the others out of here.

00:11:05.500 --> 00:11:08.375
Even with my identification skill,
I can't see its data.

00:11:08.375 --> 00:11:12.958
It's probably as strong as something from
floor 90. I'll buy you some time. So run!

00:11:12.958 --> 00:11:16.500
--Y-You come with me.
--I'll catch up later. Hurry!

00:11:19.042 --> 00:11:20.042
Mommy...

00:11:22.500 --> 00:11:23.500
Take care of Yui!

00:11:23.833 --> 00:11:25.500
You three should run!

00:11:25.500 --> 00:11:26.542
Asuna!

00:11:26.542 --> 00:11:28.625
--We can't do that...
--Hurry!

00:12:03.667 --> 00:12:04.875
Kirito!

00:12:05.125 --> 00:12:07.917
--Yui, no!
--It's dangerous... Come back!

00:12:18.583 --> 00:12:20.208
Don't be stupid!
Get out of there!

00:12:20.875 --> 00:12:21.958
Yui...

00:12:24.917 --> 00:12:27.875
It's okay... Daddy, Mommy.

00:12:29.625 --> 00:12:30.625
Yui!

00:12:37.500 --> 00:12:38.958
Immortal Object?

00:13:46.042 --> 00:13:47.875
Yui?

00:13:47.875 --> 00:13:49.667
Yui...

00:13:49.667 --> 00:13:51.708
Daddy... Mommy.

00:13:52.667 --> 00:13:55.167
I remember everything now.

00:14:00.417 --> 00:14:04.208
Yui, have you regained your
memories? About everything?

00:14:05.167 --> 00:14:06.167
Yes.

00:14:08.083 --> 00:14:09.917
Kirito. Asuna.

00:14:11.625 --> 00:14:14.917
This world, Sword Art Online,

00:14:14.917 --> 00:14:18.250
is controlled by a single,
immense system.

00:14:18.958 --> 00:14:21.250
The system is called Cardinal.

00:14:21.750 --> 00:14:26.792
This system was designed to operate
without any human intervention.

00:14:26.792 --> 00:14:31.833
It regulates the balance of SAO
according to its own discretion.

00:14:32.667 --> 00:14:37.792
From monster and NPC AI
to drop rates for items and money.

00:14:37.792 --> 00:14:42.625
Everything is controlled by the processes
executed by the Cardinal program.

00:14:43.250 --> 00:14:46.250
Even the psychological
care of the players...

00:14:47.417 --> 00:14:51.292
Mental Health Counseling
Program, prototype 1.

00:14:51.292 --> 00:14:53.083
Code name: Yui.

00:14:53.958 --> 00:14:55.208
That's me.

00:14:56.875 --> 00:14:58.083
A program?

00:14:58.625 --> 00:15:00.167
An AI?

00:15:00.917 --> 00:15:07.125
I was given the ability to emulate
emotion, to put players at ease.

00:15:08.250 --> 00:15:11.250
I'm not real... Nothing about me is.

00:15:11.250 --> 00:15:12.875
Even these tears.

00:15:13.625 --> 00:15:15.625
I'm sorry, Asuna...

00:15:16.542 --> 00:15:17.792
Yui.

00:15:22.167 --> 00:15:24.500
But you had amnesia.

00:15:24.958 --> 00:15:27.125
Can that happen to an AI?

00:15:28.250 --> 00:15:32.375
Two years ago, on the day
of the official launch...

00:15:32.375 --> 00:15:34.792
For reasons I never understood,

00:15:34.792 --> 00:15:38.542
Cardinal forbade me from interacting
with any of the players.

00:15:39.333 --> 00:15:45.042
I was forced to do nothing but continue
to monitor the players' mental states.

00:15:46.542 --> 00:15:50.500
Their mental states...
were utterly horrible.

00:15:51.875 --> 00:15:52.875
No!

00:15:57.958 --> 00:16:03.708
Terror, despair, rage. People were
overcome by negative feelings.

00:16:04.875 --> 00:16:08.667
Some of them went
completely insane.

00:16:10.833 --> 00:16:16.000
Normally, I would have gone
to them immediately.

00:16:16.542 --> 00:16:20.125
But I wasn't permitted
any contact with them.

00:16:21.125 --> 00:16:24.833
Gradually, errors accrued within me,

00:16:24.833 --> 00:16:26.583
and I fell apart.

00:16:30.167 --> 00:16:31.792
But one day,

00:16:32.167 --> 00:16:36.792
I saw two players whose
mental parameters were

00:16:36.792 --> 00:16:39.292
very different from the rest.

00:16:40.833 --> 00:16:42.833
Joy,

00:16:42.833 --> 00:16:44.083
peace...

00:16:45.125 --> 00:16:47.000
But it was more than that.

00:16:50.333 --> 00:16:52.167
I wandered through the field,

00:16:52.167 --> 00:16:57.000
hoping to get as close
to you as I could.

00:16:57.375 --> 00:16:59.958
That's why you were in
the 22nd-floor forest?

00:16:59.958 --> 00:17:00.792
Yes.

00:17:00.792 --> 00:17:02.833
Kirito, Asuna...

00:17:03.458 --> 00:17:06.583
I've always wanted to meet you.

00:17:07.167 --> 00:17:08.958
It's strange, isn't it?

00:17:08.958 --> 00:17:11.458
It should be impossible
for me to think that.

00:17:12.542 --> 00:17:15.333
I'm only a program...

00:17:17.208 --> 00:17:21.708
Yui, you have true
intelligence, don't you?

00:17:23.542 --> 00:17:26.042
I don't know.

00:17:26.667 --> 00:17:29.167
I don't know what's
happened to me.

00:17:33.500 --> 00:17:37.667
You aren't just a program that
the system controls anymore.

00:17:37.667 --> 00:17:41.167
So you should be able to say
what it is that you want.

00:17:42.167 --> 00:17:43.750
What do you want?

00:17:46.917 --> 00:17:48.250
I...

00:17:50.208 --> 00:17:51.458
I...

00:17:55.500 --> 00:17:58.125
I want to stay with you forever...

00:17:59.292 --> 00:18:00.958
Daddy, Mommy!

00:18:07.958 --> 00:18:09.208
Together...

00:18:09.208 --> 00:18:11.458
We'll be together forever, Yui.

00:18:13.208 --> 00:18:16.208
That's right. You're our child, Yui.

00:18:22.083 --> 00:18:24.333
It's too late...

00:18:25.167 --> 00:18:26.208
Too late?

00:18:27.708 --> 00:18:33.792
This console grants the GMs
emergency access to the system.

00:18:36.000 --> 00:18:39.375
I used it to delete that monster.

00:18:40.625 --> 00:18:44.375
But now it's running a
check on my program.

00:18:44.917 --> 00:18:47.625
Since I've disobeyed
Cardinal's orders,

00:18:47.625 --> 00:18:50.083
I'm considered a foreign
object in the system.

00:18:50.583 --> 00:18:53.042
I'll be deleted immediately.

00:18:53.875 --> 00:18:54.792
No...

00:18:54.792 --> 00:18:56.750
Isn't there some
way around that?

00:18:58.167 --> 00:19:00.833
Daddy, Mommy, thank you.

00:19:01.750 --> 00:19:03.167
This is goodbye.

00:19:06.625 --> 00:19:07.833
No!

00:19:07.833 --> 00:19:09.333
I don't want that!

00:19:09.542 --> 00:19:11.292
We've just started...

00:19:11.292 --> 00:19:15.333
We've just started
living together...

00:19:16.708 --> 00:19:18.417
Yui, don't go!

00:19:19.625 --> 00:19:23.917
Everyone smiles when they're
with you, Daddy, Mommy.

00:19:25.000 --> 00:19:26.208
Please...

00:19:26.667 --> 00:19:31.375
From now on, go and help
people in my place.

00:19:32.167 --> 00:19:34.125
Share your happiness.

00:19:34.125 --> 00:19:36.500
No... No!

00:19:36.500 --> 00:19:39.792
I can't smile without you...

00:19:44.333 --> 00:19:46.500
Smile, Mommy.

00:20:14.042 --> 00:20:15.375
Cardinal!

00:20:15.375 --> 00:20:17.125
No, Kayaba!

00:20:18.042 --> 00:20:21.792
Don't think things will always go
the way you want them to!

00:20:24.125 --> 00:20:25.875
Kirito, what are you...

00:20:25.875 --> 00:20:27.000
If I act now...

00:20:27.000 --> 00:20:31.000
If I act now, I can probably still use
this GM account to access the system.

00:20:41.875 --> 00:20:42.875
Kirito!

00:20:43.958 --> 00:20:45.000
Are you okay?

00:20:51.083 --> 00:20:52.833
What's this?

00:20:52.833 --> 00:20:56.208
Before Yui's admin
credentials were denied,

00:20:56.208 --> 00:21:00.208
I split off her main program and
turned it into a game object.

00:21:01.250 --> 00:21:03.000
So this is...

00:21:03.958 --> 00:21:05.958
Yui's heart.

00:21:19.292 --> 00:21:20.333
<i>Hey, Kirito...</i>

00:21:22.167 --> 00:21:26.042
<i>If the game is cleared</i>
<i>and this world ends,</i>

00:21:26.042 --> 00:21:27.583
<i>what will happen to Yui?</i>

00:21:28.833 --> 00:21:32.792
"Floor 22: Coral"
<i>Yui's data is set to save to</i>
